cus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2534638\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 07, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104zvf1665702749538.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zvf1665702749538.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zvf1665702749538.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"zvf1665702749538\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Managing Cloud LM Sessions and Tokens\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\">\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"zvf1665702749538__context_w568ab1b3b1_w569ab1b3_w570ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zvf1665702749538__p_d67334e1_d67335e1_d67336e1\">On the <a class=\"xref\" href=\"https://unifacebv.prod.sentinelcloud.com/customer/login\" rel=\"external noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Sentinel EMS Customer Portal</a>, you can view and manage all\n            active sessions using a Cloud LM license. The portal shows you the consumed count of\n            your Registration Tokens, allows you to edit Registration and Authorization Tokens,\n            monitor usage, and terminate sessions.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"zvf1665702749538__note_w574ab1b3b1b3_w575ab1b3b1_w576ab1b3_w577ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> \n                     Only administrators can view Cloud LM usage on the Sentinel EMS Portal.</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zvf1665702749538__p_d67337e1_d67338e1_d67339e1\">To view and manage Cloud LM sessions:</p>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"zvf1665702749538__li_d30023e1_d30024e1_d30025e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Log in to the EMS Customer Portal.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"zvf1665702749538__li_d30026e1_d30027e1_d30028e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"zvf1665702749538__p_d67340e1_d67341e1_d67342e1\">To view active sessions, select\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Sessions</span> on the navigation pane on the left. Here you will\n               see a list of all active sessions using a Cloud LM license. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"zvf1665702749538__note_w578ab1b3b3b3b3b1_w579ab1b3b3b3b3_w580ab1b3b3b3_w581ab1b3b3_w582ab1b3_w583ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span>  The number of active sessions listed is not representative of the\n                  consumed token count. Each license can have multiple features, and each active\n                  feature represents a session. The number of concurrent Uniface instances that can\n                  be run is determined by your Entitlement.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"p\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"zvf1665702749538__fig_s1b_l5s_jvb\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>Active sessions</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Active sessions\" aria-label=\"Open image in gallery mode\" class=\"image expandable\" data-fancy=\"gallery\" data-gallery=\"gallery\" data-remote=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/Active-sessions.png?_LANG=enus\" data-title=\"Figure 1. Active sessions\" id=\"zvf1665702749538__image_s1v_n5s_jvb\" role=\"button\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/Active-sessions.png?_LANG=enus\" style=\"cursor: pointer;\" tabindex=\"0\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"zvf1665702749538__ul_hyz_2hz_jvb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zvf1665702749538__li_d30029e1_d30030e1_d30031e1\">To filter sessions, use <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Host\n                        Name</span> and <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">User Name</span> to filter for specific\n                     hosts or users. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zvf1665702749538__li_d30032e1_d30033e1_d30034e1\">To terminate an active session, select the\n                     specific session, then click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Terminate Sessions</span>. </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"zvf1665702749538__li_d30035e1_d30036e1_d30037e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"zvf1665702749538__p_d67343e1_d67344e1_d67345e1\">To view the generated Auth Tokens, select\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Access Management &gt; Auth Tokens</span> from the navigation pane\n               on the left. Here you will see a list of Authorization Tokens, including each token's\n               Identifier, the FQDN (Fully Qualified Domain Name) of the specific machine or host,\n               the Registration Token used to generate it, and the date it was generated.  </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"zvf1665702749538__fig_hzr_c5s_jvb\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 2. </span>Auth Tokens</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Auth Tokens\" aria-label=\"Open image in gallery mode\" class=\"image expandable\" data-fancy=\"gallery\" data-gallery=\"gallery\" data-remote=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/Auth-Tokens.png?_LANG=enus\" data-title=\"Figure 2. Auth Tokens\" id=\"zvf1665702749538__image_gzp_h5s_jvb\" role=\"button\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/Auth-Tokens.png?_LANG=enus\" style=\"cursor: pointer;\" tabindex=\"0\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n<section class=\"section result body required-cleanup-multiple-ol-elements-in-topic-body\" id=\"zvf1665702749538__result_w571ab1b3b5_w572ab1b3_w573ab1\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zvf1665702749538__li_d30038e1_d30039e1_d30040e1\">To filter Auth Tokens, use the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Search</span> drop-down to select the criteria and the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Search</span> input box to filter for specific criteria.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zvf1665702749538__li_d30041e1_d30042e1_d30043e1\">To edit or delete an Auth token, use the icons in the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Actions</span> column.\n <div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"zvf1665702749538__note_w584ab1b3b5b1b3b3_w585ab1b3b5b1b3_w586ab1b3b5b1_w587ab1b3b5_w588ab1b3_w589ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> \n                        Deleting an Auth Token does not decrease the consumed count on the Registration Token, but revokes authorization to connect to the Cloud License Manager. If the Registration Token is still active, it can be used to generate another Auth Token. If the Registration Token has expired, you can extend the validity or create a new one.</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534638\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534638\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Managing Cloud LM Sessions and Tokens Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 07, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Managing Cloud LM Sessions and Tokens On the Sentinel EMS Customer Portal , you can view and manage all active sessions using a Cloud LM license. The portal shows you the consumed count of your Registration Tokens, allows you to edit Registration and Authorization Tokens, monitor usage, and terminate sessions. Note: Only administrators can view Cloud LM usage on the Sentinel EMS Portal. To view and manage Cloud LM sessions: Log in to the EMS Customer Portal. To view active sessions, select Sessions on the navigation pane on the left. Here you will see a list of all active sessions using a Cloud LM license. Note: The number of active sessions listed is not representative of the consumed token count. Each license can have multiple features, and each active feature represents a session. The number of concurrent Uniface instances that can be run is determined by your Entitlement. Figure 1. Active sessions To filter sessions, use Host Name and User Name to filter for specific hosts or users. To terminate an active session, select the specific session, then click Terminate Sessions . To view the generated Auth Tokens, select Access Management > Auth Tokens from the navigation pane on the left. Here you will see a list of Authorization Tokens, including each token's Identifier, the FQDN (Fully Qualified Domain Name) of the specific machine or host, the Registration Token used to generate it, and the date it was generated. Figure 2. Auth Tokens To filter Auth Tokens, use the Search drop-down to select the criteria and the Search input box to filter for specific criteria. To edit or delete an Auth token, use the icons in the Actions column. Note: Deleting an Auth Token does not decrease the consumed count on the Registration Token, but revokes authorization to connect to the Cloud License Manager. If the Registration Token is still active, it can be used to generate another Auth Token. If the Registration Token has expired, you can extend the validity or create a new one. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}